sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser
    participant Django as Django (web)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant McpServer as MCP Server (fastmcp)
    participant ClaudeAPI as Claude API

    User->>Browser: Type message in chat panel
    Browser->>Django: HTMX POST /dashboard/chat/ with message and session_id

    Django->>DB: SELECT McpSession WHERE user=request.user AND ended_at IS NULL
    alt No active session
        Django->>DB: INSERT McpSession with tokens_used=0\nand tokens_budget from UserProfile or MCP_SESSION_TOKEN_BUDGET
    end

    Django->>DB: READ McpSession.tokens_used and tokens_budget
    alt tokens_used >= tokens_budget
        Django-->>Browser: SSE event: budget_exhausted with used and budget counts
        Browser-->>User: Chat panel shows budget-exhausted message\nwith session reset link
    else Budget available
        Django->>McpServer: Forward message and tool context via Docker internal network
        Note over Django,McpServer: Shared-secret header MCP_INTERNAL_SECRET\nidentical auth pattern to /internal/step-status/ from BL-037

        McpServer->>ClaudeAPI: messages.create with tools:\nadd_widget, update_widget, remove_widget,\nlist_widgets, list_data_sources, preview_widget

        loop Tool call iterations 0..N
            ClaudeAPI-->>McpServer: stop_reason tool_use with tool_name and tool_input
            McpServer->>McpServer: Validate widget_type against TextChoices enum\nValidate config keys against per-type allow-list

            alt Valid tool call
                alt Mutating tool — add, update, or remove
                    McpServer->>Django: POST /internal/dashboard/widgets/ with shared-secret header
                    Django->>DB: DashboardWidget INSERT or UPDATE or DELETE
                    Django-->>McpServer: 200 with widget_id
                else Read-only tool — list or preview
                    McpServer->>Django: GET /internal/dashboard/widgets/ with shared-secret header
                    Django->>DB: SELECT DashboardWidget WHERE dashboard__owner=user
                    Django-->>McpServer: 200 with widget_type, config, and position list
                end
                McpServer-->>ClaudeAPI: tool_result with success content
            else Invalid widget_type or disallowed config key
                McpServer-->>ClaudeAPI: tool_result with is_error=true
                Note over McpServer: Injection blocked structurally — no HTML/JS path exists
            end
        end

        ClaudeAPI-->>McpServer: stop_reason end_turn with final text and token usage
        McpServer-->>Django: SSE stream with text chunks and token_delta

        Django->>DB: McpSession.tokens_used += token_delta
        Django-->>Browser: SSE stream with text chunks and updated tokens_used and tokens_budget
        Browser-->>User: Append AI message to chat history\nUpdate token indicator with new usage count

        Note over Browser: If dashboard was mutated, reload iframe:\nGET /dashboard/render/id/ triggered by HTMX
        Browser->>Django: GET /dashboard/render/id/
        Django->>DB: SELECT DashboardWidget WHERE dashboard__owner=request.user
        Django-->>Browser: Minimal HTML grid with no nav and no HTMX outside iframe\nCSP: script-src self, no unsafe-inline
        Browser-->>User: Updated dashboard visible in sandboxed iframe
    end

    opt User resets session
        User->>Browser: Click Start new session
        Browser->>Django: POST /dashboard/session/reset/
        Django->>DB: McpSession.ended_at = now() and INSERT new McpSession with tokens_used=0
        Django-->>Browser: 200 with new_session_id
        Browser-->>User: Token indicator resets to 0 of budget tokens used
    end
